headline.main: HILAIRE G.E. DEGAS, NOTED PAINTER, DIES; Artist Famous for His Scenes of Parisian Life--His "Dancers at the Bar" Sold for $87,000.

snippet: PARIS. Sept. 27.--Hilaire Germain Edgard Degas, the painter, died here today. He was a noted painter of the various phases of Parisian life, particularly the ballet and horse races.
